1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:03,160
- I want to date.

2
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:06,560
- I just feel sorry for your date
for having a silly boyfriend.

3
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:11,680
- This is our first trip together.

4
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:14,560
- Do you like it?

5
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:16,800
- I really like it.

6
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,160
- Choose a number.

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,160
- One.

8
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,120
- 10 times.

9
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:25,000
- Be careful.
Your friend might become your date.

10
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:40,520
(A white flat paper on the table.)

11
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:45,600
(We can write about our dreams, predictions,
or draw funny pictures on it.)

12
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:51,240
(We believe that
the paper will always retain its simplicity.)

13
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:55,000
(Until one night.)

14
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:02,760
(In a room where things happen innocently.)

15
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:04,920
I’m sorry.

16
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,560
I didn’t….

17
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:15,800
(Those feelings are heavier than friendship.)

18
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:23,720
(Without thinking,
I write them down and fold the paper.)

19
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:27,160
(This leaves marks on the paper.)

20
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,080
Sh*t.

21
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,480
He kissed me.

22
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:07,720
I’m sorry.

23
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,400
I didn’t mean it.

24
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,920
Did he leave?

25
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,560
Yes.

26
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,640
Really?

27
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:57,760
Yes.

28
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,080
What? You scared me.

29
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,240
Why are you that startled?

30
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:08,000
Hurry up and go to school.

31
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,440
Did Ko Song leave for school?

32
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:13,680
Yes.

33
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,360
Hey.

34
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,600
I’m going to the market.

35
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,560
Do you want me to give you a ride?

36
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,000
I’m a junior in high school.

37
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,960
I don’t need you to give me a ride to school.

38
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:21,560
Why?

39
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:26,440
You don’t want your friends
or your girlfriend to see me?

40
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,640
What girlfriend?

41
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,560
Nonsense.

42
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,400
I’ll ask Ko Song about it.

43
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,520
I’ll have him keep tabs on you.

44
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,720
Mom, just leave him alone.

45
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:38,480
Why?

46
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,320
Just leave him alone.

47
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,600
Fine, I’ll leave him alone.

48
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,040
But I won’t leave you alone.

49
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,160
Go. I’m closing the door.

50
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,640
Come on. Go.

51
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,720
Fine. I’m leaving.

52
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:52,960
I’m leaving. Goodbye, Mom.

53
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,600
Aren’t you going to kiss me before leaving?

54
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,240
Sure.

55
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,480
So cute.

56
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,080
Ride safely.

57
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,200
Yes, Mom. Goodbye.

58
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,280
Are you avoiding me?

59
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,120
How can you kiss me and disappear?

60
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:16,760
Huh?!

61
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,000
Did you say ‘kiss’?

62
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,920
Augar, you scared me.

63
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,240
I’ve got to go.

64
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,080
See you in the classroom.

65
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,440
Why are you in such a hurry?

66
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,400
Did you say ‘kiss’?

67
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,440
What?

68
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:34,200
I said I watched a cartoon
on the Kids Channel.

69
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,080
Let’s go to the classroom.

70
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,560
You are acting strange.

71
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,360
Can I sit with you?

72
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:53,840
Yeah.

73
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,000
Ko Song, are you confused
from studying too much?

74
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,160
Can I have your seat?

75
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,120
Why?

76
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,640
Did you have a fight with Ko Neung?

77
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,520
I have something to talk to Tle.

78
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,920
I want to talk to him about the science exam.

79
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:17,960
Okay.

80
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,920
I’ll sit with Ko Neung.

81
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,600
Let’s see who will fall asleep first.

82
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:25,880
I’m sleepy. I’ll sleep through the class.

83
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,280
I feel so sleepy.

84
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:30,040
Augar, this is not good.

85
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,640
Why are you sitting here today?

86
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:36,520
I don’t know.

87
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,880
If he didn’t tell me
he wanted to talk to Tle about the exam,

88
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,280
I would think you two were fighting.

89
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,520
The exam is coming soon.

90
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:47,720
Yeah.

91
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,520
Damn, since we are in Grade 11,

92
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,160
every class is getting much harder.

93
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,240
What’s wrong with your lips?

94
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:02,560
What?!

95
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,280
My lips, what?!

96
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,560
What the heck?! Do you want to get hit?

97
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,080
I saw you compress your lips.

98
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,480
I thought
there was something wrong with them.

99
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,360
Why are you going to hit me?

100
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,640
Fine.

101
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,200
I’m sorry.

102
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,480
You…

103
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,360
How was your talk with Tle about the exam?

104
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:08,720
It…

105
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:10,760
It was fine.

106
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,360
It was hard.

107
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,440
Right.

108
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,440
Achi wants us to study together at my house.

109
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,320
Do you want to come?

110
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:23,120
Sure.

111
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,520
You said you didn’t mean…

112
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,480
I’m starving.

113
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,720
I had to wait for August to buy his noodles.

114
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,720
I told you it would take a long time.

115
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,760
There was a long line at the shop.

116
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,120
I want to eat noodles.

117
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,360
Achi also waited for me.

118
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,720
He doesn’t complain, unlike you.

119
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,000
Seriously, Ko. What’s going on?

120
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:50,080
Yeah.

121
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,680
You two are acting strange.

122
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,960
Ko Song, didn’t you wait
to come to school with him this morning?

123
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,040
I…

124
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,760
No, I just…

125
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,240
I couldn’t sleep last night.

126
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:09,240
Is it because you were thinking
about finding a date?

127
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,520
It must be it.

128
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,360
You were complaining about it.

129
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,640
Are you crazy, Achi?

130
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:17,600
I just couldn’t sleep. That’s all.

131
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,040
You two are acting strange.

132
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,720
Seriously. Are you two fighting?

133
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,840
What the heck are you saying?

134
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,680
Normally, when we have lunch,
you always sit next to each other.

135
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,120
You sit together in the class.

136
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,920
You come to school together.

137
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,320
You two are joined at the hip.

138
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:39,560
But today, you two have become distant.

139
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,280
It’s not that.

140
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,760
Do you want me to sit next to him?

141
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:48,040
Should I put my arm around his shoulder
to prove that we aren’t on bad terms?

142
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:51,840
Yes.

143
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:53,560
Are you serious?

144
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,400
Didn’t you say you would do it?

145
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,520
Are you happy now?

146
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:21,480
Yeah.

147
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,280
What?

148
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,120
We are not mad at each other.

149
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:56,960
What are you doing?

150
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:17,080
Ko Song, please don’t tell August.

151
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,600
I’m afraid that…

152
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,240
Sure.

153
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:21,880
Really?

154
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:22,800
Yes.

155
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:26,120
I knew since you took a picture for us.

156
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,400
Huh?

157
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,880
When one of us asked you to do it,
you said no.

158
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,920
But when August asked,
you agreed to do it right away.

159
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:38,200
Is it that obvious?

160
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:42,960
I think he doesn’t know.

161
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:48,000
I don’t know how to approach him.

162
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,920
Ko Song, can you help me?

163
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:53,800
Sure.

164
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:58,680
Actually, he really wants to meet the person
who wrote the notes.

165
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,720
It’s amazing that
you’ve been doing this since last year.

166
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,200
Right.

167
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:09,680
When he read your note,
he said he wanted to meet you.

168
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,400
Why don’t you set up a meeting with him?

169
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,240
What are you talking about?

170
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:20,520
Ko Song, can I have my seat back now?

171
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,280
Or do you want to switch our seats for good?

172
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,560
Sure. You can have your seat back.

173
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,240
Okay.

174
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,160
Thank you.

175
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:41,320
The class monitor, don’t you miss me?

176
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,200
Do you miss me?

177
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,640
Ko Song, he doesn’t miss me.

178
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,160
Let’s switch our seats back.

179
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,320
I don’t want to sit with you.

180
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,960
Don’t chat in class.

181
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,520
You need to focus on your studies.

182
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,320
I guarantee it will be in the exam.

183
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,280
Achi, let’s play tic-tac-toe.

184
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,680
Augar, it’s not time to play.

185
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,800
(Why aren’t you studying?
Do you want to fail the exam?)

186
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,440
(I don’t want to do it.
I’ll study with our study group.)

187
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,320
(Are you still mad at me?)

188
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,040
(I’m sorry.)

189
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,680
(I know you didn’t mean it.)

190
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,000
Do you have to do everything on the list?

191
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,080
Yes.

192
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,560
But today, I’m going to practice
only shooting and ball handling.

193
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,360
I’ll shoot from here, there,
and the three-point line.

194
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,880
Usually, the team practice is tougher than this.

195
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,160
Achi, you’ve seen it before, haven’t you?

196
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,160
Yes.

197
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:35,320
But the exam is coming soon.

198
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,320
Do you still have to practice?

199
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:38,120
I’ll leave my exam score to my luck.

200
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,120
Is that also up to your luck?

201
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:52,920
What do you think?

202
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,520
You are talented. I admit it.

203
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:15,480
(If he gets a three-point shot this time,
I’ll confess my feelings to him.)

204
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,360
Augar, shoot a three-point shot again.

205
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,160
Do you still not believe
that my shooting is accurate?

206
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,000
No.

207
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,880
You’re right. It’s really up to my luck.

208
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:50,560
What did you write?

209
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,440
Nothing. I was just drawing.

210
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,480
Can you go home late today?

211
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,240
Sure, I called and told my mom

212
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:03,440
that we will have a group study
at Ko Neung’s house.

213
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:07,400
I forgot that you have a mobile phone.

214
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,240
I’m envious of rich kids.

215
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,920
Then you should date someone rich.

216
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:11,560
Huh?

217
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,000
I’m joking.

218
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,360
You have many admirers.

219
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,320
I thought you might have someone
on your mind.

220
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:18,760
I don’t have one.

221
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,440
Are you saying you can have your pick?

222
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:25,000
I’ll go get changed.

223
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:28,840
I’ll wait for you in front of the school.

224
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:29,600
Sure.

225
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,240
August.

226
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,480
When will they arrive?

227
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:48,640
I’m going to fall asleep.

228
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:49,440
Right.

229
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,520
Ko Song lives next door.

230
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,360
But he’s still not here.

231
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,880
Why don’t you go get him?

232
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,360
No need to do that.

233
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:02,880
He’ll show up when it’s time.

234
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:08,240
We can’t start studying by ourselves.

235
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,240
We both are dumb.

236
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:14,160
If we do that,
we will become the dumb and dumber.

237
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,960
Why do you call me dumb?

238
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,000
I’m talking about myself.

239
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,520
We’re here.

240
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,040
Hello.

241
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,800
Nice of you to show up.

242
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:32,320
Why wouldn’t you come tomorrow?

243
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,480
Okay, I’ll leave.

244
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:34,400
I’m just being sarcastic.

245
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,280
I’m kidding.

246
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,480
Where is Ko Song?

247
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,560
Speak of the devil.

248
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,400
Sorry. I was talking to my dad
about my tutoring class.

249
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:07,360
We have oranges from Ko Song’s house.

250
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:09,080
It’ll be hard for me to concentrate on studying.

251
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:14,720
Are you sure it is for you?

252
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,040
It’s for everyone.

253
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:26,800
Really?

254
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,800
Thanks, buddy.

255
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:31,600
I’ll have one too.

256
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,520
Can I have one too?

257
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,960
You should have brought more of it.

258
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,280
Shall we start?

259
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,360
So we don’t finish too late.

260
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,120
Damn.

261
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:07,520
What is the paper?

262
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:08,760
Is it a note from that person?

263
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:10,480
You’ve been getting them since last year.

264
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,560
Let me take a look.

265
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,320
Can you mind your own business?

266
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,400
The handwriting looks very familiar.

267
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:23,720
Who wrote it, Achi?

268
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,600
I…

269
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:27,480
What?

270
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:29,520
I’m not familiar with it.

271
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,960
You pause at the worst possible moment.

272
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,120
This person must have had a crush on you
for a long time.

273
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,480
It must be one of our classmates.

274
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,720
What makes you think that?

275
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:46,520
I just guess from what you guys said.

276
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,000
Achi said the handwriting looks familiar.

277
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:52,280
Ko Neung said the person must have had
a crush on you for a long time.

278
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,400
It means that the person sees you every day.

279
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:57,640
If that person is in another class,

280
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,760
they would have given up on you
a long time ago.

281
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,600
I think he’s right.

282
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:05,600
That person is in our class
and has had a crush on you for a long time.

283
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,280
It’s not surprising to catch feelings.

284
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,720
Let’s start our group study.

285
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:29,080
Come on.

286
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:29,880
Let’s get started.

287
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,720
Plant tissue culture.

288
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,360
Augar, you haven’t even started studying.

289
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:18,080
MIDTERM EXAM DAY

290
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,320
Why is Ko Song not here yet?

291
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:25,440
You’re right.

292
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,600
I don’t know where he is.

293
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:29,840
Where the hell is he?

294
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,760
Alright, alright.

295
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,440
You can go into the exam room now.

296
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,320
If anyone is late more than ten minutes,

297
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,360
I won’t allow them to go into the room.

298
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:59,200
If you need to go to the bathroom,
please hurry.

299
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:02,080
August, what are you praying for?

300
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,400
It won’t help you with the exam anyway.

301
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,880
Idiot, don’t copy my answers.

302
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,720
Why? Can’t I copy them?

303
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:10,560
Let’s go in.

304
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,440
You can copy my answers.

305
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,320
Let’s get in.

306
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,360
Let’s get it over with.

307
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,080
Come on.

308
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,880
It’s time for you to start doing the exam.

309
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,560
Mr. Kong, am I on time for the exam?

310
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:29,720
Okay.

311
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:30,920
Go to your seat.

312
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:48,080
Do your best, everyone.

313
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,160
The exam is so hard.

314
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:06,160
I told you, August.

315
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:07,640
Praying couldn’t help you.

316
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,120
I just randomly chose the answers.

317
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,280
Why did it take you so long? I’m starving.

318
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:15,920
Boss Ko, are you the last one
to leave the exam room?

319
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:18,520
It seems like you work hard on it.

320
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,720
Where is Ko Song?

321
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,560
I saw that he was one of the first people
to leave the exam room.

322
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,000
Where is he?

323
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:32,040
Ko Song has been acting strange lately.

324
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:34,120
Ko Neung.

325
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,600
Do you really not know
what’s going on with Ko Song?

326
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,040
Do you miss me that much?

327
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,360
How did you get in here?

328
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:51,640
What is wrong with me?

329
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,560
What the heck?!

330
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:06,280
Why?

331
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,520
Am I bothering you that much?

332
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:44,400
Can I hold you?

333
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:48,240
Why can’t I get you out of my head?

334
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,960
We have done more than this.

335
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:55,160
Get out of my head.

336
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:06,200
I can’t reach Ko Song.

337
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,480
Where is he?

338
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:13,600
I remember Ko Song said
he’s attending a cram school in Bangkok.

339
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,600
Right, Ko Neung?

340
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:18,400
Damn, if you don’t eat it, I will.

341
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,240
It’s melting.

342
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:21,080
Stay away from my ice cream.

343
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,840
He always does things without telling us.

344
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:25,960
Forget about him.

345
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,000
Aren’t you worried about him?

346
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:33,320
He is attending a cram school.

347
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,160
What if he’s not?

348
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:36,320
What if…

349
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:40,680
he’s kidnapped by a human trafficking gang
or he has an accident?

350
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,560
Watch your mouth.

351
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:43,680
August, it hurts.

352
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:45,280
Are my lips busted?

353
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:48,280
I can’t tell.

354
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:49,240
Your lips have the same color
as the ice cream.

355
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,640
August, damn you.

356
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,640
Did you find out who wrote you those notes?

357
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:55,960
No.

358
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,480
The note says they will come to see me.

359
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:01,400
You might have met your admirer,
but you just didn’t know it.

360
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:02,840
Very funny.

361
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:04,720
I’m only hanging out with you guys.

362
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:09,000
If you didn’t write the notes to tease me,
then I don’t know who it is.

363
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:16,160
Ko Neung, why don’t you ask Ko Song’s Dad
how he is doing?

364
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:17,840
Fine.

365
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,520
I’ll ask him when I have free time.

366
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,720
Jackass, you said like you are busy.

367
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,360
I don’t see you doing anything.

368
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:25,320
Do you want to get your lips busted?

369
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,680
Why are guys around here so rough?

370
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,080
Aren’t we in a playground?

371
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:33,960
Here.

372
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,160
Thanks.

373
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,120
Augar.

374
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:43,240
I got this from my senior
who studies sports science.

375
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:48,360
What is this?

376
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,880
It’s a checklist for his college team’s practice
for the national team tryout.

377
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:52,240
Do you want me to practice
like a college athlete?

378
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:56,480
I can’t even get into the youth team.

379
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:59,240
It’s not bad to know it in advance, right?

380
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,240
I know you are serious about it.

381
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,600
Achi, you are the best. Thank you.

382
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,320
-Don’t.
-Achi, you are the best. Thank you.

383
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,240
Am I too dirty for you right now?

384
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:07,880
Don’t touch me.

385
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:08,920
You are sticky.

386
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:09,560
I’m not sticky.

387
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:10,160
You are sticky.

388
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,480
Achi, don’t run away from me.

389
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:13,360
Am I too dirty for you?

390
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:13,960
Aren’t we friends?

391
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:16,520
No, you’re sticky. Don’t touch me.

392
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:17,600
It’s not that bad, Achi.

393
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:23,360
You already told me that you didn’t mean it.

394
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:30,120
If you miss me the same way I miss you,
can you send me a sign?

395
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:37,720
Ko, is that you?

396
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:39,400
Ko, is that you?

397
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,360
Hello, Dad.

398
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:44,320
Hello.

399
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:46,120
Ko is not home.

400
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:47,520
He went to Bangkok to attend a cram school.

401
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:49,560
Yes.

402
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:53,680
Do you know…

403
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,840
when he will come back?

404
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:58,120
Shortly before the school starts.

405
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,200
How can I contact him?

406
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:05,440
Our friends are asking about him.

407
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:06,360
It’s better not to contact him.

408
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:09,400
He said he doesn’t like to be interrupted
when he is studying.

409
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:10,840
Right.

410
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,760
What are you doing?

411
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:15,800
Do you need my help?

412
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,560
There’s a bird nest on the branch.

413
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:22,720
I helped Ko Song make it
when we were in Grade 10.

414
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:27,400
But I think the baby birds are all grown up
and have already left the nest.

415
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:28,960
Why did you do such a dangerous thing?

416
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,960
You could have gotten injured
if you had fallen out of the tree.

417
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:32,200
Right.

418
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,200
Dad.

419
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,880
Ko Song…

420
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:40,880
Is it his idea to attend the cram school?

421
00:30:45,320 --> 00:30:46,600
Yes. Why?

422
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:48,680
No, nothing.

423
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:16,560
♪ Every time that we meet again ♪

424
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:20,840
♪ Something grows a little more each day ♪

425
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:25,360
♪ The closer we are,
the more I feel the love I’ve waited for ♪

426
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:29,120
♪ Might not be too far away at all ♪

427
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:32,680
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

428
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:36,360
♪ Till the final raindrop falls,
hope is never gone ♪

429
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:41,080
♪ As long as I have you holding my hand
as we walk on ♪

430
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:48,160
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

431
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:51,520
2ND SEMESTER OF GRADE 11

432
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:56,680
Mom.

433
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,600
Are you going to feed the whole neighborhood?

434
00:31:58,600 --> 00:31:59,960
I made the meal for your dad too.

435
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:00,920
He will come home soon.

436
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:16,440
Why aren’t you friend coming in?

437
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,480
Go invite him to have breakfast with us.

438
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,560
Ko.

439
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,880
Tell him to have breakfast with us.

440
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,160
What are you saying?

441
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:35,440
Fine.

442
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:43,200
Come in.

443
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:56,520
Come in, sweetie.

444
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,680
My mom told me to give you this orange cake.

445
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:03,680
Thank you.

446
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:07,720
You are handsome and sweet, Ko Song.

447
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:12,080
How do you know that Ko likes orange cake?

448
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:16,760
Come on. Join us for breakfast.

449
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,680
I already ate.

450
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:20,840
I’ve got to go.

451
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:21,720
Alright.

452
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,760
Are you avoiding me?

453
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:57,080
Am I right?

454
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,760
I’m short-sighted. I can’t see the blackboard.

455
00:34:05,520 --> 00:34:06,160
Okay

456
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,560
You chose to do this.

457
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:08,840
This is what you want, right?

458
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:26,080
Damn it.

459
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:27,720
What the hell is going on?

460
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:29,400
Augar, you see it, right?

461
00:34:29,680 --> 00:34:32,040
They have been acting strange
since before the school break.

462
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:34,040
There must be a problem between them.

463
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:35,440
I’ll follow him.

464
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,640
Ko Song.

465
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:45,120
Don’t you know that if you do this,
things will get worse?

466
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,960
I don’t know
what’s going on between you two,

467
00:34:52,240 --> 00:34:54,080
but Ko Neung tries to approach you.

468
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:57,120
But you suddenly changed.

469
00:34:57,640 --> 00:34:58,920
You’re driving him mad.

470
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:01,600
Don’t do this.

471
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:05,200
I can tell that he really cares about you.

472
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:29,200
How is he?

473
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:31,000
He told me to leave him alone.

474
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,200
I don’t get it.

475
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:40,360
Why are you and I on cleaning duty today?

476
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:43,040
It’s the first day at school, but it’s raining.

477
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,280
My umbrella is broken.

478
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:48,160
It’s good that we are on duty today.

479
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,840
Not many students attend classes today.

480
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,320
So the room is not that dirty.

481
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:55,080
Think about it, our next cleaning schedule
is another 15 days.

482
00:35:55,120 --> 00:35:58,160
Imagine how dirty the classroom will be.

483
00:35:58,280 --> 00:35:59,200
It will be more tiring to clean it.

484
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:00,360
Fine, I’m sorry.

485
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:01,520
I’m just venting.

486
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,120
I don’t want to know your reason.

487
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:10,440
Hey.

488
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:14,280
Tle, do you like being a class monitor?

489
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:18,200
Do you like to say “Class, stand up”?

490
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:24,840
What?

491
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:46,960
Hey.

492
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,040
I’ll be right back.

493
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:01,360
I don’t know how things are going to be
between Ko Neung and Ko Song.

494
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:03,400
Me too.

495
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:05,200
They are acting childishly.

496
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:10,000
I think they must have feelings for each other.

497
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:11,120
They are always joined at the hip.

498
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:14,600
Yes, they are coward.

499
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,800
They are probably afraid
to lose their friendship.

500
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:24,880
I think it takes a lot of courage
to confess your feelings to someone.

501
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:27,440
Don’t they feel uncomfortable
with the situation?

502
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,680
Yes, probably.

503
00:37:30,160 --> 00:37:32,600
Not everyone can speak their mind like you.

504
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:35,600
What about you, Achi?

505
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:36,480
Do you speak your mind?

506
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,040
I don’t know.

507
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:50,800
Today, I’ll follow your senior’s practice checklist.

508
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:51,760
Can you help me check the list?

509
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:52,760
Sure.

510
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:17,880
Toey.

511
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:23,560
Can you give this umbrella to Ko Neung?

512
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:31,360
It’s his umbrella, not mine.

513
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:40,840
Ko.

514
00:38:43,080 --> 00:38:44,400
Ko Song told me to give it to you.

515
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,600
He said it’s your umbrella.

516
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:47,640
Is that so?

517
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:11,720
Ko Song.

518
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:13,160
Ko.

519
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:17,720
Can’t you just say what is on your mind?

520
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:28,080
I’m sorry.

521
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,360
That’s all you can say?

522
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:36,840
I’m sick of your apologies.

523
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:39,880
You keep saying sorry again and again.

524
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:41,680
That’s all you do.

525
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:51,520
Do you think it’s right
for you to keep avoiding me?

526
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:01,400
Can you stop driving me crazy, Ko Song?

527
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,320
Listen to me.

528
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,320
What happened in your room that night,

529
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:17,760
it didn’t frustrate me
as much as your action right now.

530
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:25,360
Do you think I will stop being your friend?

531
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:27,600
It’s not like that.

532
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,840
I admit that I was stunned
and didn’t know what to do.

533
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:40,040
When you apologized to me
and told me you didn’t mean it.

534
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:42,160
I’m okay with it.

535
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:44,080
You didn’t mean it, and it’s okay.

536
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:46,120
But what the hell are you doing?

537
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,120
After you apologized to me,
you suddenly changed.

538
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:52,960
Why are you keeping your distance from me?

539
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,280
Answer me!

540
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,320
Why?!

541
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:00,040
Tell me!

542
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:10,240
Fine.

543
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:15,000
If you don’t want to talk to me,
then don’t ever speak to me again.

544
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:19,080
I like you.

545
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:26,880
(Our life begins as an empty paper.)

546
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,440
(No one can tell…)

547
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:36,400
(what words will be written on it.)

548
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:42,000
♪ Distance only makes me think it over ♪

549
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:49,520
♪ What should be said
if we again meet each other ♪

550
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:53,120
♪ Will say “I love you” ♪

551
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:57,880
(Until we start to write or fold the paper
to leave marks on it.)

552
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:01,480
I LIKE YOU.

553
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:02,840
(Someone writes their feelings down.)

554
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,440
(Because they want to get to know someone.)

555
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:06,760
It’s me. I sent you those notes.

556
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,000
IF I SCORE A THREE-POINT SHOT,
(Someone writes their feelings down directly.)

557
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,600
I’LL CONFESS MY FEELINGS TO YOU.
(Someone writes their feelings down directly.)

558
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:30,160
(Someone writes their feelings down
because they feel comfortable.)

559
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:33,600
(If the paper has folding marks,)

560
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:38,160
(it doesn’t mean it can no longer be used.)

561
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,800
(They will always remind us)

562
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:46,160
(that's how strong
our feelings for each other once were.)

563
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:49,200
♪ Will say "I love you" ♪

564
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:55,200
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

565
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:59,840
♪ No more watching from afar,
letting chances go ♪

566
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:02,680
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

567
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:06,760
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪

568
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:11,400
- He kissed me.

569
00:43:11,560 --> 00:43:11,920
- Huh?

570
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:15,400
- If you keep thinking about it,
doesn’t it mean that you…

571
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,760
- I’m not sure.

572
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:19,760
- Have you two reconciled?

573
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:23,800
- Do you remember
that you two used to be enemies?

574
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:28,000
- Didn’t you promise me
that you won’t disappear again?

575
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:30,720
- Can we go back to being what we used to be?

576
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:32,400
- Here.

577
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,160
- Do you want to go to my room to play games?

